@startuml
!define AWSPUML https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v14.0/dist
!include AWSPUML/AWSCommon.puml

title AWS Real-Time Use Cases Repository - Deployment and Control Flow

actor "Developer/Architect" as User
participant "GitHub Repository" as Repo
participant "Use Case Catalog" as Catalog
participant "Template System" as Template
participant "Metadata Aggregator" as Metadata
participant "External Resources" as External
participant "AWS Documentation" as AWSDoc
participant "Udemy Courses" as Udemy
participant "Community System" as Community

== Use Case Discovery Phase ==
User -> Repo: Access repository
activate Repo
Repo -> Catalog: Browse use cases
activate Catalog
Catalog -> Catalog: Filter by difficulty level\n(100-500)
Catalog -> Catalog: Categorize by AWS domain\n(Security, Storage, Compute, etc.)
Catalog --> User: Display available use cases
deactivate Catalog

== Use Case Selection and Learning ==
User -> Catalog: Select specific use case
activate Catalog
Catalog -> Repo: Load use case README.md
activate Repo
Repo -> Metadata: Extract metadata
activate Metadata
Metadata -> Metadata: Parse problem statement
Metadata -> Metadata: Parse solution details
Metadata -> Metadata: Parse next steps
Metadata --> Catalog: Return structured content
deactivate Metadata

Catalog -> Repo: Load architecture images\nfrom /images/ directory
Repo --> Catalog: Return diagrams
deactivate Repo

Catalog --> User: Present use case with\narchitecture diagrams
deactivate Catalog

== External Resource Navigation ==
User -> Metadata: Request additional learning resources
activate Metadata
Metadata -> External: Aggregate external links
activate External
External -> AWSDoc: Link to AWS documentation
activate AWSDoc
AWSDoc --> External: Return documentation URLs
deactivate AWSDoc

External -> Udemy: Link to related courses
activate Udemy
Udemy --> External: Return course URLs
deactivate Udemy

External --> Metadata: Consolidated resource links
deactivate External
Metadata --> User: Provide curated learning paths
deactivate Metadata

== Community Contribution Flow ==
User -> Community: Initiate contribution
activate Community
Community -> Template: Request use case template
activate Template
Template -> Repo: Load templates/README.md
activate Repo
Repo --> Template: Return template structure
deactivate Repo

Template --> Community: Provide structured template\n(Difficulty-Level-Domain-Title)
deactivate Template

Community --> User: Template with required fields:\n- Problem statement\n- Solutions\n- Next steps\n- Metadata\n- Images
deactivate Community

User -> User: Author new use case\nfollowing template

== Use Case Submission and Integration ==
User -> Repo: Submit pull request with\nnew use case
activate Repo
Repo -> Template: Validate structure
activate Template
Template -> Template: Check naming convention\n(DIFFICULTY-DOMAIN-TITLE)
Template -> Template: Verify required sections
Template -> Template: Validate metadata format
Template --> Repo: Validation results
deactivate Template

Repo -> Catalog: Integrate new use case
activate Catalog
Catalog -> Catalog: Add to difficulty category
Catalog -> Catalog: Tag by AWS domain
Catalog -> Metadata: Register metadata links
activate Metadata
Metadata -> Metadata: Index external resources
Metadata --> Catalog: Confirm registration
deactivate Metadata
Catalog --> Repo: Integration complete
deactivate Catalog

Repo --> User: Merge and publish use case
deactivate Repo

== Ongoing Learning and Support ==
User -> Community: Access interview topics
activate Community
Community -> Repo: Load templates/interview_topics.md
activate Repo
Repo --> Community: Return discussion outline
deactivate Repo
Community --> User: Provide experience-sharing framework
deactivate Community

User -> Repo: Support via ko_fi funding
activate Repo
Repo -> Community: Process donation
activate Community
Community --> Repo: Acknowledge contribution
deactivate Community
Repo --> User: Confirmation
deactivate Repo

@enduml
